Grammy award-winning singer, Burna Boy has given his personal definition of true love. The singer, via his Twitter handle, shared several reasons why he doesn’t believe any lady ever loves him genuinely. According to Odogwu, the emotions of fear and pure love which the grandma displays at every point in time heightens his disbelief for the ladies’ ‘love’ even more and makes it harder to settle with just any one.   Cubana Priest rains money on Rick Ross     Icezy sets to release new single ‘Body Riddim’     Veteran highlife singer Orlando Julius dies   The self-acclaimed ‘African Giant” further emphasised that the love of his Grandma who he described as his ‘everything’ is his definition of true love. “Just in Amsterdam doing sound check and all I can think of is “I need my grandma everywhere I go” but that woman cannot understand/handle fans screaming and touching me, or seeing me stressed without crying so hard out of genuine fear and love. “My Everything!! She is probably the reason I don’t believe any girl Loves me. I know what true love feels like.. Grandma’s Love,” Burna tweeted.